INSERT INTO `sys_oper_log` (`oper_id`, `title`, `business_type`, `method`, `request_method`, `operator_type`, `oper_name`, `dept_name`, `oper_url`, `oper_ip`, `oper_location`, `oper_param`, `json_result`, `status`, `error_msg`, `oper_time`) VALUES (554, '文章管理', 1, 'com.zaaac.cms.blog.controller.CmsBlogController.add()', 'POST', 1, 'Zac', NULL, '/cms/blog', '134.195.146.217', 'XX XX', '{\"tagIds\":[27,29,31],\"title\":\"Building My Personal Blog from Scratch (Vue + Node + Nginx Deployment)\",\"type\":\"1\",\"content\":\"<h1>s</h1>\",\"top\":\"1\",\"blogDesc\":\"A full walkthrough of building and deploying my pe\",\"contentType\":\"1\",\"blogPicType\":\"0\",\"contentMarkdown\":\"# Building My Personal Blog from Scratch (Vue + Node + Nginx Deployment)\\n\\n\\nAs a developer, I’ve always wanted to have my **own personal blog platform** — not just for writing articles, but also to share my learning notes, project experiences, and even some lifestyle stories. So I decided to build one from scratch. This post documents the process.\\n\\n\\n----\\n\\n## 🚀 Features\\n\\n\\n1. **Blog Management**\\n\\t- Add, edit, and delete posts\\n\\t- Assign tags and categories\\n\\t- Rich text editing with Quill Editor\\n\\n2. **Cover & Description**\\n\\t- Each post supports a cover image (upload or URL)\\n\\t- Short descriptions for post previews\\n\\n3. **Tag System**\\n\\t- Posts can have multiple tags (e.g., Vue, React, Python, Travel, Food)\\n\\t- Tag-based filtering for easy browsing\\n\\n4. **Category Management**\\n\\t- Each post belongs to one category (Tech, Life, Travel, etc.)\\n\\t- Categories displayed in navigation\\n\\n5. **Pinning Feature**\\n\\t- Important posts can be pinned at the top of the homepage\\n\\n\\n----\\n\\n## 🛠️ Tech Stack\\n\\n\\n- **Frontend**: Vue 3 + Element UI\\n\\n- **Backend**: Node.js / FastAPI (API support)\\n\\n- **Database**: MySQL (for posts, categories, users)\\n\\n- **Deployment**: Nginx reverse proxy, static file hosting, Node.js service with `screen`\\n\\n\\n----\\n\\n## 📂 Deployment Steps\\n\\n\\n1. **Build frontend**\\n\\t```\\n\\tcd frontend\\n\\tnpm install\\n\\tnpm run build\\n\\t```\\n\\tThis generates the `dist/` folder.\\n\\n2. **Upload to server**\\n\\t```\\n\\tscp -r dist/* root@your_server:/home/ZacBlog/frontend/\\n\\t```\\n\\n3. **Configure Nginx**\\n\\t```\\n\\tserver {\\n\\t    listen 80;\\n\\t    server_name zaaac.vip;\\n\\t    location / {\\n\\t        root /home/ZacBlog/frontend;\\n\\t        index index.html;\\n\\t        try_file', NULL, 1, '\n### Error updating database.  Cause: com.mysql.cj.jdbc.exceptions.MysqlDataTruncation: Data truncation: Data too long for column \'title\' at row 1\n### The error may exist in URL [jar:file:/home/ZacBlog/backend/zaaac-admin.jar!/BOOT-INF/lib/zaaac-cms-3.8.0.jar!/mapper/cms/CmsBlogMapper.xml]\n### The error may involve com.zaaac.cms.blog.mapper.CmsBlogMapper.insertCmsBlog-Inline\n### The error occurred while setting parameters\n### SQL: insert into cms_blog          ( create_by,             create_time,                                       title,             type,             content,             content_type,             content_markdown,             Top,                          status,             blog_pic_type,                                       blog_desc )           values ( ?,             ?,                                       ?,             ?,             ?,             ?,             ?,             ?,                          ?,             ?,                                       ? )\n### Cause: com.mysql.cj.jdbc.exceptions.MysqlDataTruncation: Data truncation: Data too long for column \'title\' at row 1\n; Data truncation: Data too long for column \'title\' at row 1; nested exception is com.mysql.cj.jdbc.exceptions.MysqlDataTruncation: Data truncation: Data too long for column \'title\' at row 1', '2025-10-01 15:18:00');
